Task 2 — Import Launch Template and Auto Scaling Group
Step 1 — Add import blocks

Append to imports.tf:
# imports.tf (append)

import {
  to = aws_launch_template.example
  id = "lt-0f5566dcbc56782b9"
}

import {
  to = aws_autoscaling_group.example
  id = "testASG"
}
⚠️ Important: The ASG import ID is always the ASG Name (testASG), NOT the Launch Template ID.

Step 2 — Generate config for both resources
terraform plan -generate-config-out=generated2.tf

Step 3 — Fix conflicting attributes in generated2.tf
The auto-generated ASG config will contain the following conflicts that must be removed/commented out:
# ❌ REMOVE — conflicts with vpc_zone_identifier
availability_zones = ["ap-south-1a"]

# Inside launch_template block:
# ❌ REMOVE — cannot use both id and name together
name = "MyTemplate"

Your cleaned generated2.tf should have the ASG block like this:

resource "aws_launch_template" "example" {
  name          = "MyTemplate"
  image_id      = data.aws_ami.example.id
  instance_type = "t3.micro"
  vpc_security_group_ids = ["sg-0fa8ffd50a836f572"]
}

resource "aws_autoscaling_group" "example" {
  name             = "testASG"
  desired_capacity = 1
  min_size         = 1
  max_size         = 1

  # ✅ Only vpc_zone_identifier — availability_zones removed
  vpc_zone_identifier = ["subnet-xxxxxxxx"]

  launch_template {
    id      = aws_launch_template.example.id   # ✅ only id, name removed
    version = "$Default"
  }
}

Step 4 — Run terraform plan

terraform plan

Expected output:
data.aws_ami.example: Reading...
data.aws_ami.example: Read complete after 1s [id=ami-05d2d839d4f73aafb]
